article.description: Kevin Zabo scored 24 points and Adonis De La Rosa scored on a jump hook with 21 seconds remaining to lead Kent State past Ohio 70-69 on Friday night.
article.headline: Zabo, De La Rosa spark Kent State to 70-69 victory
article.linkText: Zabo, De La Rosa spark Kent State to 70-69 victory
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- Kevin Zabo scored 24 points and Adonis De La Rosa scored on a jump hook with 21 seconds remaining to lead Kent State past Ohio 70-69 on Friday night. Kent led 37-31 at halftime before Ohio (8-8, 1/3 Mid-American) rallied and tied it at 67-all with 2:40 remaining on Gavin Block's 3-pointer. Teyvion Kirk layup gave the Bobcats a 69-68 lead with two minutes left. De La Rosa scored for the lead and Zabo went to the line with three seconds left. He missed the first free throw, and, after a Kent State timeout, ricocheted the second off the front of the rim and back to himself and he dribbled out the clock. Zabo made four 3-pointers and the Golden Flashes (8-9, 2-2) sank 8 of 18 from the arc. Kirk scored 17 points to lead Ohio with Mike Laster adding 11 and Block and Jordan Dartis 10 each.
